{{Quote|The Force-using tradition of the Jarvashqiine extends to the earliest centuries of the Republic. Their shamans believed that the dark side can manifest itself only through elaborate blood rituals. But removing these atavistic rites can actually block a Jarvashqiine adept's ability to use the Force.|Restelly Quist, ''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force''|<ref name="JP">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>}}
The '''Jarvashqiine''' were a group of [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]]-like [[Priest/Legends|priests]]<ref name="CSWE" /> who were [[Force-sensitive/Legends|able]] to use [[Force power/Legends|abilities]] granted by [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and adhered to its [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]].<ref name="JP" /> They were worshipped by a religion of the [[Jarvashqiine|same name]]<ref name="CSWE" /> and believed that only the use of elaborate [[Blood/Legends|blood]] rituals allowed the dark side to manifest itself; in truth, the absence of such rituals could render a Jarvashqiine priest unable to access the Force at all.<ref name="JP" />

In [[990 BBY]],<ref name="JP" /><ref name="990 BBY">{{Blogspot|subdomain=geekosity|url=2010/12/endnotes-for-star-wars-jedi-path-part-1.html|name=Daniel Wallace's Geekosity|text=Endnotes for Star Wars: The Jedi Path (part 1 of 4)|quote=Okay, so we've established that this particular copy of the book dates from 115 BBY. But the content inside is [&hellip;] dating from the year 990 BBY.}}</ref> [[Chief Librarian/Legends|Chief Librarian]] [[Restelly Quist/Legends|Restelly Quist]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] mentioned the Jarvashqiine in the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jedi training/Legends|trainee]] [[Book/Legends|guidebook]] ''[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force]]'', describing the rituals used by the priests as "atavistic."<ref name="JP" /> At some point after the [[Declaration of a New Order|foundation]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]<ref name="DES">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref> in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]] and [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Sith Lord]]<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] studied the shamanism of the Jarvashqiine in an attempt to attain complete mastery over the Force and its dark side.<ref name="DES" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Jarvashqiine shamans were first indirectly referred to as the "shamanism of Jarvashqiine" in the ''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'', [[Michael Allen Horne]]'s [[1993]] sourcebook published by [[West End Games]] for use with ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="DES" /> [[2008]]'s ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' subsequently established that "Jarvashqiine" was a term that applied to both the religion and its shaman-like priests.<ref name="CSWE" />

